quran[17]{c,v,t,f}:
  103,1,"By the time,",""
  103,2,"man is in utter loss,",""
  103,3,"except those who believe and do righteous deeds, and exhort one another to the truth and exhort one another to patience.",""
  104,1,"Woe to every backbiter and slanderer,",""
  104,2,"who amasses wealth and counts it over and again<sup>1</sup>,","[1] Instead of spending in the way of Allah."
  104,3,"thinking that his wealth will make him live forever.",""
  104,4,"No indeed! He will surely be cast into the Crushing Fire<sup>2</sup>,","[2] i.e., Hellfire, as it crushes and destroys all that is thrown in it."
  104,5,"and how do you know what the Crushing Fire is?",""
  104,6,"It is the kindled Fire of Allah,",""
  104,7,"which reaches the hearts<sup>3</sup>.","[3] Penetrating through bodies and reaching the hearts."
  104,8,"It will be closed down upon them,",""
  104,9,"locked with towering columns<sup>4</sup>.","[4] i.e., columns of fire or columns of iron to which the inmates of Hell are chained."
  105,1,"Have you not seen how your Lord dealt with the people of the Elephant<sup>1</sup>?","[1] The army of Abrahah al-Ashram was accompanied by a huge elephant who came with the intention of demolishing the Ka øba."
  105,2,"Did He not turn their scheme into a total loss<sup>2</sup>?","[2] Leading them to perish."
  105,3,"He sent against them swarms of birds,",""
  105,4,"pelting them with stones of baked clay,",""
  105,5,"leaving them like chewed-up chaff.",""
